abstract: Republican U.S. Senator Lisa Murkowski, an unpredictable moderate in a polarized Washington, on Monday declared she will vote to acquit Donald Trump, but not before leveling an attack against the president and fellow lawmakers of both parties during a partisan impeachment ordeal.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican U.S. Senator Lisa Murkowski, an unpredictable moderate in a polarized Washington, on Monday declared she will vote to acquit Donald Trump, but not before leveling an attack against the president and fellow lawmakers of both parties during a partisan impeachment ordeal.
headline_main: Republican Senator Murkowski Spares Few in Fiery Impeachment Speech

abstract: Like many Iowans, Peggy Magner is still grappling with a weighty choice as the state's first-in-the-nation nominating contest fast approaches: which Democratic candidate is best equipped to defeat Republican President Donald Trump in November.
snippet: Like many Iowans, Peggy Magner is still grappling with a weighty choice as the state's first-in-the-nation nominating contest fast approaches: which Democratic candidate is best equipped to defeat Republican President Donald Trump in November.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — Like many Iowans, Peggy Magner is still grappling with a weighty choice as the state's first-in-the-nation nominating contest fast approaches: which Democratic candidate is best equipped to defeat Republican President Donald Trump in November.
headline_main: Ahead of Crucial Vote, Anxious Iowa Democrats Grapple With Tough Choices
headline_print_headline: Ahead of Crucial Vote, Anxious Iowa Democrats Grapple With Tough Choices

abstract: Iowa's Democrats promised to begin to release long-delayed results on Tuesday afternoon from the party's chaotic first voting in its process of picking a candidate to face Republican Donald Trump in November's U.S. presidential election.
snippet: Iowa's Democrats promised to begin to release long-delayed results on Tuesday afternoon from the party's chaotic first voting in its process of picking a candidate to face Republican Donald Trump in November's U.S. presidential election.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Iowa's Democrats promised to begin to release long-delayed results on Tuesday afternoon from the party's chaotic first voting in its process of picking a candidate to face Republican Donald Trump in November's U.S. presidential election.
headline_main: Iowa Democrats to Release First Results After Presidential Caucus Chaos
headline_print_headline: Iowa Democrats to Release First Results After Presidential Caucus Chaos

abstract: Bernie Sanders' campaign had built up what it described as the largest California operation of any Democratic presidential candidate - until billionaire Mike Bloomberg made a late entry into the race in November with seemingly bottomless resources.
snippet: Bernie Sanders' campaign had built up what it described as the largest California operation of any Democratic presidential candidate - until billionaire Mike Bloomberg made a late entry into the race in November with seemingly bottomless resources...
lead_paragraph: SACRAMENTO, Calif. — Bernie Sanders' campaign had built up what it described as the largest California operation of any Democratic presidential candidate - until billionaire Mike Bloomberg made a late entry into the race in November with seemingly bottomless resources.
headline_main: As Democrats Fight for Iowa, Bloomberg Makes a Play for Delegate-Rich California
headline_print_headline: As Democrats Fight for Iowa, Bloomberg Makes a Play for Delegate-Rich California

abstract: Even with acquittal seemingly assured, Democrats prosecuting President Donald Trump in his impeachment trial made a forceful appeal for conviction on Monday, calling him a man with no moral compass who must be removed to protect American democracy.

headline_main: Democrats Condemn Trump at Trial as Threat to American Democracy

abstract: Caroline Kennedy, the daughter of President John F. Kennedy, endorsed Joe Biden on Tuesday, calling the former vice president Democrats' “best bet to win the White House.”
snippet: Caroline Kennedy, the daughter of President John F. Kennedy, endorsed Joe Biden on Tuesday, calling the former vice president Democrats' “best bet to win the White House.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Caroline Kennedy, the daughter of President John F. Kennedy, endorsed Joe Biden on Tuesday, calling the former vice president Democrats' “best bet to win the White House.”
headline_main: Caroline Kennedy Backs Biden, Calls Him Democrats' Best Bet
headline_print_headline: Caroline Kennedy Backs Biden, Calls Him Democrats' Best Bet

abstract: We’re moving on to New Hampshire, but we’re still stuck in Iowa. This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: We’re moving on to New Hampshire, but we’re still stuck in Iowa. This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: No winner emerged from the Iowa caucuses last night. But, in the wee hours of the morning, at least one thing became official: In 2020, we cannot have nice things.
